com.strandgenomics.imaging.iclient
Class PixelData

java.lang.Object
  com.strandgenomics.imaging.iclient.ImageSpaceObject
      com.strandgenomics.imaging.iclient.PixelData
All Implemented Interfaces:
Disposable, ImageSource, IPixelData, Serializable
public class PixelData
extends ImageSpaceObject
implements IPixelData

An pixel-data (raw bitmap image) within a record is uniquely identified by the 4 dimensions - (slices, frames, sites, channels) in addition to its x and y coordinates. All this 4 numbers starts with 1 and the last value is limited by the size in each corresponding dimensions

Author:
arunabha

PixelData

PixelData(Record parent,
          Dimension imageID,
          double x,
          double y,
          double z,
          double elapsedTime,
          double exposureTime,
          Date timeStamp)
Construct a PixelData Object instance from the information made available from the underlying system

Parameters:
parentRecord - the parent record
imageID - record dimensions that uniquely identify this pixel-data
x - X coordinate in micron, default is 0
y - Y coordinate in micron, default is 0
z - Z coordinate in micron, default is 0
elapsedTime - time in milliseconds from the beginning of the acquisition phase
exposureTime - the exposure time (of this image) in milli-seconds
timeStamp - the creation time (when the image was captured)
gridRow - the grid row coordinate
gridColumn - the grid column coordinate
blackContrast - Contrast level for black
whiteContrast - Contrast level for white
gammaContrast - Contrast level for gamma
baseRGB - the RGB base color of the image - default: Gray (128, 128, 128)
